while((newLine=f.readLine()) != null){
    StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer(newLine);
    while(st.hasMoreTokens()){
        int i1 = Integer.parseInt(st.nextToken());
        System.out.println("Adding to list"+i1);
        input.add(i1);
    }
}
<<<explanation>>>:
The StringTokenizer class has a method called hasMoreTokens() which returns true if there are more tokens to be read.

A: You can use the hasMoreTokens() method to check if there are more tokens to be read.
while((newLine=f.readLine()) != null){
    StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer(newLine);
    while(st.hasMoreTokens()){
